article.headline: E. Kentucky 49, Jacksonville St. 37
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Orlandus Harris caught two touchdowns and had 205 yards receiving to help Eastern Kentucky snap Jacksonville State's 12-game winning streak, 49-37 on Saturday night. The streak was the longest in the Football Championship Subdivision and second longest in all of college football next to Boise State's 22 straight wins. Harris, who had four catches, put the Colonels (4-5, 3-2 Ohio Valley Conference) ahead for good, 14-10, on a 44-yard touchdown catch from T.J. Pryor with 3:57 left in the second quarter. Pryor had two touchdowns passing and another on the ground. Harris followed with a 76-yard catch from wide receiver Justin Williams. In a game that had a combined 915 yards of total offense, Eastern Kentucky held Jacksonville State (8-1, 5-1) to just 28 yards rushing. Marques Ivory was 30-for-49 with one interception, three touchdowns and 444 yards for the Gamecocks.
